I"‚<p>##How do I set up my own Facebook App?</p>

<p>Facebook logins work out of the box with CT WiFi. However, some people want to use their own application. The benefits of this include:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Your customers see your logo, not ours</li>
  <li>You can control the permissions</li>
</ul>

<p>Thereâ€™s some information about checkins about the bottom of this page.</p>

<h3 id="getting-started">Getting Started.</h3>

<p>First up, you need a Facebook account. Once you have this, head over to the Facebook developer portal and create an account. The developer site is here:</p>

<p><a href="https://developers.facebook.com">https://developers.facebook.com</a></p>

<h3 id="create-an-app">Create an App.</h3>

<p>Click the <em>My Apps</em> button, then click <em>Add New App</em></p>

<div class="mdl-typography--text-center">
  <img src="/images/community/tutorials/facebook-logins/facebook-captive-portal-1.png" width="300px" />
</div>

<p>On the following screen, select the website option.</p>

<div class="mdl-typography--text-center">
  <img src="/images/community/tutorials/facebook-logins/facebook-captive-portal-2.png" width="800px" />
</div>

<p>Enter a name for your new application. Make it clear, keep it simple. Click <strong>Create New Facebook App ID</strong>.</p>

<p>Choose a category and then click <strong>Create App ID</strong></p>

<div class="mdl-typography--text-center">
  <img src="/images/community/tutorials/facebook-logins/facebook-captive-portal-3.png" width="800px" />
</div>

<div class="mdl-typography--text-center">
  <img src="/images/community/tutorials/facebook-logins/facebook-captive-portal-4.png" width="800px" />
</div>

<p>Scroll down and enter the url for your login pages - it must match your actual login pages. For example, acme.my-wifi.co</p>

<div class="mdl-typography--text-center">
  <img src="/images/community/tutorials/facebook-logins/facebook-captive-portal-5.png" width="800px" />
</div>

<p>Once this is done, refresh the page and select your application from the <em>My Apps</em> dropdown. It will look something like this.</p>

<div class="mdl-typography--text-center">
  <img src="/images/community/tutorials/facebook-logins/facebook-captive-portal-6.png" width="800px" />
</div>

<h3 id="the-settings">The Settings.</h3>

<p>Fill-in your settings, exactly as per the screenshots below. Make sure youâ€™re using the correct url - you can use the brand youâ€™ve already probably set-up in your Cucumber dashboard. It has to match your login pages.</p>

<p>Youâ€™ll also need to add your own logo and support email.</p>

<div class="mdl-typography--text-center">
  <img src="/images/community/tutorials/facebook-logins/facebook-captive-portal-7.png" width="800px" />
</div>

<h3 id="add-application-to-ct-wifi">Add Application To CT WiFi</h3>

<p>Youâ€™re almost done, you can now test your application.</p>

<p>Login to your dashboard and navigate to one of your locations. Click splash pages (or create a new one)!</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>Enable social logins and scroll down to the Facebook options.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Uncheck <strong>Use our credentials</strong></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Enter your App ID in the box (youâ€™ll find this in your Facebook developer portal).</p>
  </li>
</ul>

<div class="mdl-typography--text-center">
  <img src="/images/community/tutorials/facebook-logins/facebook-captive-portal-8.png" width="800px" />
</div>

<h3 id="testing-testing-testing">Testing Testing Testing</h3>

<p>Open up a login page and make sure you can see the social login screen. Click Facebook and login - you should see a new popup prompting you to enter your credentials. If this doesnâ€™t work, please check you have entered your URL correctly and that your App ID matches your Facebook App.</p>

<p><strong>Please note, you will not be able to checkin yet. You need to apply to Facebook for this privilege.</strong></p>

<h3 id="status-and-review">Status and Review</h3>

<p>Ok, happy that your new application is working? You probably want your users to checkin now.</p>

<p>To checkin at a location, you now need to tag a place in your Open Graph story (more info on this at the bottom). You donâ€™t need to worry too much about the logistics, weâ€™ll do that for you. All you need is the correct permissions for your application.</p>

<p>In your Facebook developerâ€™s portal, head over to <strong>Status &amp; Review</strong>. Please make sure your Application is live. An email is required to activate it.</p>

<p>Once this is done, make sure the Approved Items are all green and then click the <strong>Start a New Application</strong> button.</p>

<div class="mdl-typography--text-center">
  <img src="/images/community/tutorials/facebook-logins/facebook-captive-portal-9.png" width="800px" />
</div>

<p>You need to apply for <strong>publish_actions</strong>. If the following banner appears, please make sure youâ€™ve actually logged in once via the new app.</p>

<div class="mdl-typography--text-center">
  <img src="/images/community/tutorials/facebook-logins/facebook-captive-portal-10.png" width="800px" />
</div>

<p>Fill-in all the required information on the following page. In the <strong>Facebook Login Integration</strong> box, explain the following:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Youâ€™re a Wi-Fi hotspot provider.</li>
  <li>Youâ€™re allowing the users to checkin after they have logged in.</li>
  <li>Mention that checkins are optional and any messages are optional too.</li>
</ul>

<p>If you have the time, please take some screenshots of your login pages and the checkin form.</p>

<p><strong>Itâ€™s really important youâ€™re clear that the user doesnâ€™t have to checkin. If you donâ€™t say this, your application may be refused.</strong></p>

<p>Once youâ€™re done, click submit. Get yourself some tea and wait. It may take a couple of days to get your Application approved.</p>

<div class="mdl-typography--text-center">
  <img src="/images/community/tutorials/facebook-logins/facebook-captive-portal-11.png" width="800px" />
</div>

<h3 id="test-test-test">Test Test Test</h3>

<p>Once your application is approved, you should head off and check you can now checkin! Your developer portal should also look like this:</p>

<div class="mdl-typography--text-center">
  <img src="/images/community/tutorials/facebook-logins/facebook-captive-portal-20.png" width="800px" />
